How to create an ad set?

To create an ad set on NewsBreak, follow these steps:
1. Log in to your NewsBreak advertiser account.
2. Navigate to the 'Ad Management' tab.
3. Click on 'Create Ad Set'.
4. Fill out the details for your ad set, including targeting options and budget.
5. Save and submit your ad set for approval.
For more detailed instructions, you can refer to this article: [How to create your first ad](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17618196971149-How-to-create-your-first-ad).

To create an ad on NewsBreak, follow these steps:
1. Access Ad Management.
2. Click 'Create Campaign.'
3. Choose the objective that aligns with your goal, such as brand awareness, website traffic, or app installs. Make sure to hit 'Save and Next.'
4. Select your targeting options based on location, gender, age, user interest, etc.
5. Define how long you want your campaign to run and set your budget (minimum daily budget is $10).
6. Fill in your creatives by adding a headline, body text, image/video, and link to your listing.
For more detailed instructions, you can refer to this article: [How to create your first ad](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17618196971149-How-to-create-your-first-ad).
